  {
    "type": "message",
    "subtype": "thread_broadcast",
    "text": "Interesting. Are there other ways than documentation that foster collaboration? Something less tiresome to maintain.",
    "user": "UCKRZS3DZ",
    "ts": "1542182643.027000",
    "thread_ts": "1542143526.025900",
    "root": {
      "client_msg_id": "7688e2b8-a0ec-44dd-b767-a527d70c6473",
      "type": "message",
      "text": "Yeah, I should elaborate. Well-written documentation can be _great_ for collaboration. But well-written documentation can be _really_ hard to do, _even_ when the incentives are perfectly aligned (very rare even in open source; the world is complex). So lately I try to at least talk about the thing right in front of the thing rather than on some other page all by itself. That way at least if I screw up how I describe the thing, at least the reader has a chance at trying to cross-triangulate what I mean by looking at and running the thing itself.\n\nBut you're a Smalltalk guy. I suspect I'm preaching to the choir :slightly_smiling_face:",
      "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
      "ts": "1542143526.025900",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "thread_ts": "1542143526.025900",
      "reply_count": 1,
      "reply_users_count": 1,
